\
Applications of Outlier Detection\
	1.	Fraud Detection\
Detecting unusual patterns in financial transactions or network activities to identify fraudulent behavior.\
	2.	Quality Control\
Identifying defective products in manufacturing by detecting anomalies in sensor data.\
	3.	Medical Diagnosis\
Finding unusual test results that may indicate rare diseases or abnormalities in patient health.\
\
Conclusion\
Outlier detection plays a critical role in ensuring data integrity and model performance. Identifying and handling outliers properly allows analysts and data scientists to extract meaningful insights from datasets and build more accurate models. Whether for fraud detection, quality control, or medical diagnosis, outlier detection is an indispensable tool in data analysis.}